                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 1:54:06 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> For <br /><br />1. Conjuration Based To offset max damage Alteration would of made us higher dps than rogues with ubber gear on the melee side.<br /><br />2. Alot of mana: Well of course they just jumped you FT 15 in one spell. They were going to increase spells accordingly.  Even with increased mana use on spells overall mana produced is higher.<br /><br />3. Alot of agro: True just have to be smart and know when to use it I use it on most named in elemental planes.  Agro management now is tough so you have to watch yourself like any other class.  Lucky necros get 4 agro reducers.<br /><br />4. Rune spell (this is our best dot? O_o)We made off better than shamans.<br /><br />Blood of Saryrn   <br />Slot Description <br />1:  Increase Poison Counter by 9 <br /><b>2:  Decrease Hitpoints by 320 per tick</b>  <br /><b>Mana: 535</b> Skill: Conjuration <br /><b>Casting Time: 5.7</b> Recast Time: 2.25 <br />Fizzle Time: 2.5 Resist: Poison <br />Range: 200 Location: Any <br />Push Back 0.5 Deletable: No Dot Stacking: Yes <br />Interruptable: Yes Short Buff Box: No <br />Target Type: Single Spell Type: Detrimental <br />Source: Test 04/04   <br />Classes: SHM/65 <br />Duration: 7 ticks <br /><br />Blood of Thule  <br />Slot Description <br />1:  Increase Poison Counter by 9 <br /><b>2:  Decrease Hitpoints by 335 per tick</b><br /><b>Mana: 500</b> Skill: Conjuration <br /><b>Casting Time: 5</b> Recast Time: 2.25 <br />Fizzle Time: 2.5 Resist: Poison <br /><b> Adjust -50</b> 200 <br />Location: Any Time of Day: Any <br />Push Back 0.5 Deletable: No <br />Dot Stacking: Yes Interruptable: Yes <br />Short Buff Box: No Target Type: Single <br />Spell Type: Detrimental Source: Test 04/04 <br />  <br />Classes: NEC/65 <br />Duration: 7 ticks <br /><br />5. Why not just chain Neurotoxin cause its:<br />a. instant damage: Short damage yup neuro all the way long term BoT is <br />b. less agro Neuro can get you summoned and killed after a few casts too.<br />c. alteration and more efficient especially <br />if it crits:  Main reason is (BoT)56+(pyre)44+(DP)22+(Kiss)33=155dps that doesnt take into account the rest of your dots or your pet.  Pyre + Bot = 110 dps If BoT was alter you would be looking at sustainable dps far far higher than a rogue ranger or monk.  I don't believe SoE was ready to have necros a higher dps class than a rogue so the made it poison so the checks against specialization would balance out with the mana used. <br /><br />(I wont argue that the spell has its uses and value. Although its still a huge disapointment. I think the sadest thing is that this is our best 65 spell now... Neurotoxin &gt; BoT hands down. If you dont think so just ask yourself which one you would rather have...)<br /><br />Neurotoxin is used for short fights mainly on stuff dead in 1 min or less.  IN any fight over 1 min just doesnt make sense your looking at 1300(25%max added damage)(38% less mana)(crit for 20% max) for 465 compared to 2200(25% added damage)(18% less mana) for 500 mana.  <br /><br />Necros wanted a faster dot, they wanted more dps, well VI gave them to us at a price.  With all the mana reducers out there they used conjur to offset that.  If you hate it being conjur switch specialization to conjur.  Unfortunatly we cant get our cake and eat it too.  Necro overall dps is at a all time high in raids. Once they add the feature that will display per tick dot damage we will see how much some of the leaders of our class are producing.  Overall BoT is a better spell than pyre specially since 1 zone out of 4 in elemental planes is fire unfriendly. During xp i use them both and they are good additions to my spell book.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Lich Brendayan Arch Lich<br />Morell-Thule<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.htm