                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/09/2003&nbsp;: 12:17:47 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> BoT is disappointing as the reward for achieving level 65, when in all prior cases the penultimate level (level 60) is where all the "best" spells were - Funeral Pyre, Arch Lich, Zevfeers Theft of Vitae, Ancients, etc.  BoT is NOT a better spell than Funeral Pyre.  Funeral Pyre is resisted less, has better DPM, and is alteration.  BoT is a nice replacement for Pyre in positions where every mob is fire immune, and it complements Funeral Pyre quite well if you want to only cast 2-3 DoTs on a mob.  However, this does not leaven it from the grasp of mediocrity, especially considering the amount of aggro it generates on raids, wherein you'll have to FD much more, and thus be less efficient. (both DPS and DPM-wise)<br /><br />This would not really matter if any of the other level 65 spells were FP-quality, but none of them are.  CoB is more or less broken.  WOT has been broken in the latest patch.  Destroy Undead is nice, but there aren't very many undead mobs in PoP outside of CoDecay.  <br /><br />It seems to me the Power Levels of a PoP necro are levels 61-64, with 65 being a nice touch, but not really required.  Having level 65 be the "weakest" level is a departure from previous standards, and thus obviously some people are upset.<br /><br />Saryrn's Kiss is the best DoT we received in PoP in my mind.  Dark Plague & BoT are both disappointing, but whereas DP is store-bought and thus expected to be mediocre, BoT is a high-end rune-drop, and by definition should own FP.  Yet it doesn't.<br /><br />I agree, the disparity between DoTs & DDs in general is the PRIMARY problem, but the relative mediocrity of our DoTs in PoP is at least secondary in the decay of DoTs and the rise of DDs to the point where necros have, essentially, become nukers.<br /><br /><br /><br />Etadanik the Redeemed</span></font></td>
